The paper proposes a method for image classification using eye-movement scanpaths, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The study involves participants reading news articles and rating them as relevant or irrelevant, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The method uses a convolutional neural network classifier, which is a popular machine learning technique (cs.LG). The goal is to predict perceived-relevance of news articles, which is a task in information retrieval (cs.IR).
